<!--\'b6 22.--> Art appreciation and religious conversion were one. By the same token, for the minority art making and religious redemption must have been one. Actually, by the time it appeared among them, the religious state of mind that they were feeling had already taken a symbolic form in an especially symbolic Buddhism. When they propagated this faith to other persons to save them, they necessarily had to make real these symbols.\
