<!--\'b6 23.--> Their method for doing so was none other than art. Because of this, the priests had to become artists. Or said the other way, even if someone were an authentic artist, for that person's desire to create art to bear fruit, that person certainly had to become either a priest or a passionate believer. This is a peculiar example of the close correlation of idol veneration and art making. Just as art appreciation develops its root sources out of the inner life of its makers, idol veneration also develops from the inner life of idol makers. We must be increasingly respectful of the creators among our ancestors. \
